job_detail:
Aeolus Robotics Inc. is seeking for a highly motivated Process Manager who has a demonstrated track record in building teams through effective and strong leadership and managing the activities related to product troubleshooting & support for an organization. You are required to plan and execute innovative support strategies to increase the recognition of our products.
Mandatory: This position requires native-level Mandarin proficiency
This role is based in Taipei (Taiwan). Candidates must be located in Taiwan already. 

Job Responsibilities:

•	Assist to build a Product Troubleshooting & Support (PTS) team:

o	Ensuring teams provide a positive support experience, which includes being responsive to our field engineers/distributors and effectively partnering with stakeholders on the most critical problems for Aeolus Robotic customers;
o	Provides technical document support to field engineers, technicians, and product support personnel who are diagnosing, troubleshooting, repairing, and debugging complex electro/mechanical equipment lists, computer systems, complex software, or networked and/or wireless systems;
o	Manage the troubleshooting documentation to ensure troubleshooting problems can be resolved by replication, duplication and diagnostic support document;
o	Extend the area of support from the application to the environment, operating system, database and network;


•	Planning and execution of innovative support strategies;
•	Providing regular status reports from the site, facility and manufacturing;
•	Managing the Product information and troubleshooting document is up-to-date;
•	Work directly with our most relevant internal groups to drive Product support and troubleshooting documentation and change release note that enhance the customer experience;
•	Review SITE issues with the field engineer and distributor to update the product support document;
•	Identify, document, and resolve customer issues; escalate critical SITE questions and issues to the correspondent team and management;
•	Provide inputs to the designing team on customer feedback on new product improvements;
•	Provide guidance and products to process teams, field resources, and executive initiatives.

other:
Job Requirements:

Qualifications:
•	10+ years of working experience in product based companies;
•	5+ years experience in Product Support and Customer Service;
•	Degree in Engineering/Business Administration/IT or related field;
•	Good English communication skills, particularly in written English;
•	Advanced or Native-Level Mandarin fluency.

Mandatory Requirements
•	Experience in building teams;
•	Experience working in technical support or customer service;
•	Demonstrated experience driving service process to successful conclusions;
•	Ability to plan and execute innovative support strategies;
•	Expertise in project management methodologies and tools, traditional and/or agile (JIRA);
•	Excellent communication skills and time-management skills.
Preferred Requirements

•	Strong history of owning the end-to-end product development life-cycle spanning multiple stakeholders and groups.

Benefits
•	Getting experience in a world-class robotics company;
•	International working environment;
•	Access to company know-how, the possibility of getting great help when learning new robotics stuff.

Company Description

Aeolus Robotics is a fast-growing robotics company deploying robotic services in a broad range of industries. Our advanced robotic capabilities are already commercialized for hospitals, hotels, and eldercare facilities. We currently provide intelligent robot services in Japan and will soon expand to Europe and the US.

We are an international company with development centers around the world. Come do ground-breaking work with us on general-purpose service robotics in unstructured human spaces. We invite you to visit our careers page (http://aeolusbot.com/careers) to start growing with us.

job_detail:
Aeolus Robotics Inc. is seeking a highly motivated Failure Analysis Engineer who has demonstrated analytical thinking, computer proficiency, innovation, and problem-solving characteristics to perform the failure analysis related to an abnormal electrical and mechanical hardware issue occurring during the product development stage and also the after-MP stage to support the thorough failure analysis. This role will be responsible for product failure analysis to identify the cause of failure, testing and diagnosing products, storing files about failure analysis, and making recommendations. 

Mandatory: This position requires native-level Mandarin proficiency

This role is based in Taipei (Taiwan). Candidates must be located in Taiwan already. 

Job Responsibilities:

•	Failure analysis:
o	To characterize Robot and accessories hardware and identify the root cause of failures;
o	System-level defect analysis and recording the troubleshooting process with the technical writer;
o	Able to deep dive in the EE/ ME physical debug area.
•	Process and product quality improvement:
o	To carry out various kinds of failure/defect analysis, failure analysis technicians support various kinds of characterization measurements and at the same time continuously learn new characterization techniques;
o	An independent solution provider to share professional suggestions and follow up on the issue fixing;
o	Incorporate automation and improvement of the failure analysis process;
o	Improve testing techniques/procedures for analyzing system failure data efficiently.
•	Analysis data report:
o	To create and maintain a thorough understanding of all documented processes and procedures, including developing records and performing various failure analyses on the product and components to identify the root causes;
o	Generate the Failure analysis report monthly and go through the report with the developer and stakeholders.
•	Teamwork:
o	Collaborate with cross-functional engineering teams to review customers’ issues, and provide improvement plans to resolve the issues in a timely manner;
o	Work with DIT and FDA teams to identify action plans to drive toward conclusions. Analysis and troubleshooting during the process;
o	Team player with excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to work with international teams.

